    "pages": [
        {
            "type": "patchouli:text",
            "title": "Introduction",
            "anchor": "intro",
            "text": "If you are tired of drinking directly out of streams and ponds like a wild horse then consider making a $(item)Drinking Vessel!$()$(br2)Everytime you drink from a vessel you will consume 100mb of fluid and damage the vessel 1 durability (If applicable) or has a chance of breaking (If applicable. Can be changed in TFC server config)."
        },
        {
            "type": "patchouli:text",
            "text": "Drinking from a container will also work for passing on drink effects from $(item)Alcohol$() or other fluids. As well as $(l:tfc:cooking/food_and_water#nutrients)Nutrient$() values.$(br2)$(o)$(7)Some drinking containers can even be played as a musical instrument when empty.$()"
        },
